{The Grand Slam Chess Final was based on an idea from tennis. Wijk aan Zee,
Linares and Sofia were regarded as Grand Slam tournaments. The Final was
played from 1 until 13 ix 2008. Participants were Aronian, Anand and Ivanchuk
(winners of Wijk aan Zee, Morelia/Linares and Sofia 2008), Carlsen and Topalov
(second places) and Radjabov (two third places). The prize money was 400,000
euro.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O
8. c3 d5 9. exd5 Nxd5 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 11. Rxe5 c6 12. d4 Bd6 13. Re1 Qh4 14. g3
Qh3 15. Be3 Bg4 16. Qd3 Rae8 17. Nd2 Re6 18. Qf1 Qh5 19. f3 Rf6 20. Qe2 $5 ({
Known is} 20. Bd1) (20. Qg2 $1 {will be played in the Marshall Attack later.})
20... Bxf3 21. Nxf3 Rxf3 22. Bxd5 Qxd5 23. Bf2 Rf6 24. b3 $5 Qf5 25. Rad1 h5 $1
{Black takes the initiative.} 26. Rd3 h4 27. Re3 Rg6 28. c4 hxg3 29. hxg3 bxc4
30. bxc4 c5 $5 31. Qf3 $5 Qh3 32. Qg2 Qd7 33. dxc5 $6 {
The centre should remain closed.} (33. d5 $1 {keeps the equality.}) 33... Bxc5
34. Re4 Qc7 35. Kh2 Rh6+ 36. Kg1 Rf6 37. Be3 $6 Rd8 $1 38. Kh2 Bxe3 39. R4xe3
Rh6+ 40. Kg1 Qc5 $1 {Ivanchuk continues the attack.} (40... Qxc4 41. Re8+ Rxe8
42. Rxe8+ Kh7 43. Qe4+ Qxe4 44. Rxe4 Rd6 45. Ra4 {draws (Marin).}) 41. Qf2 Qh5
42. Qg2 Rd2 43. Re8+ Kh7 44. R8e2 ({Not} 44. Qxd2 $2 Qh1+ 45. Kf2 Qh2+ $1 46.
Ke3 Qxg3+ 47. Ke2 Qg4+ $1 48. Kd3 Rd6+) 44... Qc5+ 45. Qf2 Rxe2 46. Rxe2 $2 {
White gives a pawn.} ({Better is} 46. Qxc5 $1 Rxe1+ 47. Kg2) 46... Qxc4 47.
Qf5+ g6 48. Qe4 Qc5+ $2 (48... Qc1+ $1 49. Re1 Qb2 50. Qe2 Qd4+ 51. Qe3 Qd5 $1
52. Qe4 Qxa2 {wins a second pawn.}) 49. Kg2 Rh5 50. Rc2 Qb6 51. Rd2 Rb5 52. a4
Rb4 53. Qe7 Qc6+ 54. Kh2 Rb7 55. Qh4+ Kg7 56. Qd4+ f6 57. a5 g5 58. Qd5 Qb5 {
Anand survived in the endgame.} 1/2-1/2

